{"article_id":"KdcsJdEvK2ekmo01","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"The Benghazi committee , in the course of its investigation , discovered","depth":5},{"id":1,"text":"that Mrs. Clinton had used her personal email account for State Department business .","depth":5},{"id":2,"text":"Mrs. Clinton has said for months","depth":6},{"id":3,"text":"that she kept no classified information on the private server","depth":8},{"id":4,"text":"she had set up in her house","depth":8},{"id":5,"text":"so that she would not have to carry both a personal phone and a work phone .","depth":7},{"id":6,"text":"Her campaign said on Friday","depth":6},{"id":7,"text":"that any government secrets","depth":8},{"id":8,"text":"found on the server","depth":8},{"id":9,"text":"had been classified after the fact .","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"Campaigning in Iowa on Saturday ,","depth":5},{"id":11,"text":"she was asked about the email issue .","depth":5},{"id":12,"text":"\" I think","depth":10},{"id":13,"text":"there ' s so much confusion around this","depth":10},{"id":14,"text":"that I understand","depth":10},{"id":15,"text":"why reporters and the public are asking questions ,","depth":10},{"id":16,"text":"but the facts are pretty clear , \"","depth":9},{"id":17,"text":"she told reporters ,","depth":9},{"id":18,"text":"according to The Associated Press .","depth":7},{"id":19,"text":"\" I did not send nor receive anything","depth":7},{"id":20,"text":"that was classified at the time . \"","depth":7},{"id":21,"text":"But the two inspectors general said on Friday","depth":8},{"id":22,"text":"that the information","depth":11},{"id":23,"text":"they found","depth":11},{"id":24,"text":"was classified","depth":11},{"id":25,"text":"when it was sent","depth":11},{"id":26,"text":"and remains so .","depth":9},{"id":27,"text":"Information is considered classified","depth":8},{"id":28,"text":"if its disclosure would be likely to harm national security .","depth":8},{"id":29,"text":"The investigators said","depth":8},{"id":30,"text":"the information was not marked as classified","depth":9},{"id":31,"text":"but should have been stored only on government computer networks with special safeguards .","depth":9},{"id":32,"text":"\" This classified information never should have been transmitted via an unclassified personal system , \"","depth":8},{"id":33,"text":"Steve A. Linick , the State Department inspector general , said in a statement","depth":9},{"id":34,"text":"signed by him and I. Charles McCullough III , the inspector general for the intelligence agencies .","depth":9},{"id":35,"text":"Saturday ' s testy back-and-forth seemed to boil down to a spat","depth":4},{"id":36,"text":"about who should have announced Mrs. Clinton ' s agreement","depth":5},{"id":37,"text":"to testify .","depth":5},{"id":38,"text":"It also pointed up","depth":4},{"id":39,"text":"how contentious the subject of her email account remains","depth":5},{"id":40,"text":"- and that it is only likely to grow","depth":6},{"id":41,"text":"as 2016 draws near .","depth":6},{"id":42,"text":"The Oct. 22 date would give the committee months","depth":3},{"id":43,"text":"to receive from the State Department ,","depth":5},{"id":44,"text":"and then digest ,","depth":5},{"id":45,"text":"troves of email traffic","depth":5},{"id":46,"text":"involving Mrs. Clinton ' s aides .","depth":5},{"id":47,"text":"And her testimony would take place","depth":3},{"id":48,"text":"when more people were focused on her campaign .","depth":3}],"relations":[{"parent":97,"left":90,"right":96,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":90,"left":83,"right":89,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":83,"left":58,"right":82,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":58,"left":50,"right":57,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":50,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":57,"left":53,"right":56,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":53,"left":2,"right":52,"relation":"attr